The paper proposes a deep-learning-based method for detecting events from time series signals, specifically seismic signals. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method uses a region-based convolutional neural network, which is commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) for object detection. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of densely connected blocks, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks for image classification (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of contextual information to enrich features, which is a technique commonly used in signal processing (cs.SI).
